---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../../site';
---

<Base lang="en" title="About — Almohannad Alsbeai" altPath="/about" current="/en/about">
  <div class="wrap">
    <header class="page-head">
      <h1>About</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="prose measure" style="margin-inline: 0" data-pagefind-body>
      <img class="portrait" src="/images/almohannad-portrait.jpg" alt="Almohannad Alsbeai" width="210" height="210" loading="eager" />
      <p>
        I'm Almohannad Alsbeai — a customer experience leader, author, and speaker. I've
        spent more than seventeen years in marketing research and customer experience,
        across logistics, banking, fintech, FMCG, telecom, IT, and the public sector. I
        was born and raised in Saudi Arabia and work from Riyadh today — a long, close
        view of the region's consumers that gives me a deep feel for the local culture and
        its nuances.
      </p>
      <p>
        I began in marketing research — running 100+ quantitative and qualitative studies
        at <strong>Synovate/Ipsos</strong> for local and global brands, then leading the
        research team at <strong>Elm</strong>. From there I moved into building and leading
        customer experience from the ground up at <strong>Al Rajhi Bank</strong>, the
        <strong>Saudi Export Development Authority</strong>, <strong>Shawarmer</strong>,
        <strong>Tweeq</strong>, and <strong>Rewaa</strong>. Today I lead customer experience
        at <strong>Thmanyah</strong>, the Arabic new-media company; before that I headed CX
        at <strong>Jisr</strong>, and served on the board of the
        <strong>Customer Institute</strong> in Germany. My mission hasn't changed: business
        growth as the result of exceptional experiences that turn customers into advocates,
        and a culture that is customer-centric in practice, not in slogans.
      </p>
      <h2>Career highlights</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>17+ years across marketing research and customer experience — in logistics, banking, fintech, FMCG, telecom, retail, and the public sector.</li>
        <li>Started at FedEx, then Synovate/Ipsos, managing 100+ studies for brands like STC, Nestlé, Nokia, and Hyundai under the ESOMAR/MRS code of conduct.</li>
        <li>Led CX programs at Al Rajhi Bank — including the SAMA customer-experience benchmarking project — and trained 250+ frontline staff at Shawarmer.</li>
        <li>BSc in Information Technology (MIS) from Philadelphia University, Jordan, with continuous learning through programs from McKinsey, IBM, and CX University.</li>
        <li>Co-authored the Voice of the Customer chapter of the CXPA Book of Knowledge, and has written 90+ articles in the field.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Why I write</h2>
      <p>
        I've written about customer experience and marketing research in Arabic for years,
        because Arabic content in this field still falls short of what our region deserves.
        You'll find dozens of articles in the <a href="/en/articles">articles section</a>,
        and I've published practitioner guides including "Managing Marketing Research on
        the Client Side," "The Marketing Concept Writing Guide," and "Customer Experience
        as a Career Path," plus a contribution to the collective "CX Management Foundation
        Guide." My books are published in Arabic — see the <a href="/books">books page</a>.
      </p>
      <h2>What I believe about this craft</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Frameworks are adapted to an organization's context and culture — never copy-pasted.</li>
        <li>Metrics are a means, not an end. A score without an understanding of its drivers is report decoration.</li>
        <li>Customer-care data — complaints, requests, tickets — is a goldmine most CX teams undervalue.</li>
        <li>A recommendation that doesn't turn into a clear action — who does what, by when — isn't a recommendation.</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        Find me on <a href={SITE.linkedin} target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>, or
        join the <a href="/en/newsletter">newsletter</a> to get new writing first.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div style="height: 3rem"></div>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .portrait {
    float: left;
    width: 270px;
    max-width: 40%;
    height: auto;
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    margin: 0.4rem 2rem 1.2rem 0;
  }
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .portrait {
      float: none;
      display: block;
      width: 230px;
      max-width: 72%;
      margin: 0 auto 1.8rem;
    }
  }
</style>
